HEADWORD: Whinchat
<hw>Whin"chat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called because
it frequents <ets>whins</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
warbler (<spn>Pratincola rubetra</spn>) common in Europe; -- called also
<altname>whinchacker</altname>, <altname>whincheck</altname>,
<altname>whin-clocharet</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whine</ent>⟦br⟧
